    "initial_abstraction": "Adjusted curve-number method: S0.20 = 1000/CN - 10 inches; S0.05 = 1.33 \u00d7 S0.20^1.15; Ia = 0.05 \u00d7 S0.05.",
    "direct_runoff": "Q = (P - 0.05S0.05)^2 / (P + 0.95S0.05) when P > 0.05S0.05; otherwise Q = 0.",
    "terrain": "USGS 3DEP elevation and slope sampled within supplied watershed polygon",
    "lag": "NRCS watershed lag equation using the traditional CN retention term; hydraulic length approximated from supplied pour point and basin extent.",
    "warning": "Parameters are screening estimates. Radar rainfall, curve numbers, routing, channel transmission loss, and pool storage require field calibration; results are not measured streamflow or observed pool depth."
